SIMPLE: aggrandizement
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aggrandizement
<hw>Ag*gran"dize*ment</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>agrandissement</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of aggrandizing, or the
state of being aggrandized or exalted in power, rank, honor, or wealth;
exaltation; enlargement; <as>as, the emperor seeks only the
<ex>aggrandizement</ex> of his own family</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Augmentation; exaltation; enlargement;
advancement; promotion; preferment.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aggrandizer</ent>⟦br⟧
